{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875792550,"sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a720cec001GIDzLLDRuJo0Fs","messageID":"msg_d7a71e7b5001aDNBj0MbW6Hr29","sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6dd1b1acb50344a5b11b52a6fcff9b5f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI\n2: \n3: A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n4: \n5: ## Installation\n6: \n7: ```bash\n8: pip install agentcube\n9: ```\n10: \n11: Or install from source:\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: cd cmd/cli\n15: pip install -e .\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Usage\n19: \n20: The CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.\n21: \n22: ### Pack Command\n23: \n24: Package an agent workspace by validating and preparing it:\n25: \n26: ```bash\n27: kubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n28: ```\n29: \n30: Options:\n31: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n32: - `--agent-name TEXT`: Override the agent name\n33: - `--language [python|java]`: Programming language\n34: - `--entrypoint TEXT`: Override the entrypoint command\n35: - `--port INTEGER`: Port to expose in the Dockerfile\n36: - `--build-mode [local|cloud]`: Build strategy\n37: - `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n38: - `--output PATH`: Output path for packaged workspace\n39: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n40: \n41: Example:\n42: \n43: ```bash\n44: kubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent --language python --port 8080\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ### Build Command\n48: \n49: Build a container image from the packaged agent workspace:\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: kubectl-agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n53: ```\n54: \n55: Options:\n56: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n57: - `-p, --proxy TEXT`: Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n58: - `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n59: - `--output PATH`: Output path for build artifacts\n60: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n61: \n62: Example:\n63: \n64: ```bash\n65: kubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Publish Command\n69: \n70: Publish an agent to the specified provider:\n71: \n72: ```bash\n73: kubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n74: ```\n75: \n76: Options:\n77: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n78: - `--version TEXT`: Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n79: - `--image-url TEXT`: Image repository URL\n80: - `--image-username TEXT`: Username for image repository\n81: - `--image-password TEXT`: Password for image repository\n82: - `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n83: - `--region TEXT`: Deployment region\n84: - `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n85: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n86: - `--node-port INTEGER`: Specific NodePort for K8s deployment\n87: - `--replicas INTEGER`: Number of replicas for K8s deployment\n88: - `--namespace TEXT`: The namespace for the deployment\n89: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n90: \n91: Example:\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080 --replicas 3\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### Invoke Command\n98: \n99: Invoke a published agent with the given payload:\n100: \n101: ```bash\n102: kubectl-agentcube invoke [OPTIONS]\n103: ```\n104: \n105: Options:\n106: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n107: - `--payload TEXT`: JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n108: - `--header TEXT`: Custom HTTP headers (can be specified multiple times)\n109: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n110: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n111: \n112: Example:\n113: \n114: ```bash\n115: kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello\"}' --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ### Status Command\n119: \n120: Get the status of a published agent:\n121: \n122: ```bash\n123: kubectl-agentcube status [OPTIONS]\n124: ```\n125: \n126: Options:\n127: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n128: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n129: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n130: \n131: Example:\n132: \n133: ```bash\n134: kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ## Metadata File\n138: \n139: The CLI uses an `agent_metadata.yaml` file to store agent configuration:\n140: \n141: ```yaml\n142: agent_name: my-agent\n143: description: My AI agent\n144: language: python\n145: entrypoint: python main.py\n146: port: 8080\n147: build_mode: local\n148: region: us-west-1\n149: version: 0.1.0\n150: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ## Development\n154: \n155: ### Running Tests\n156: \n157: ```bash\n158: pytest tests/\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### Code Quality\n162: \n163: ```bash\n164: ruff check agentcube/\n165: mypy agentcube/\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ## License\n169: \n170: Apache-2.0\n\n(End of file - total 170 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI\n\nA developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube\n```\n\nOr install from source:\n\n```bash\ncd cmd/cli\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md","time":{"start":1775875792526,"end":1775875792549}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875792555,"sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7218b6001jcdKltBoWPuRQt","messageID":"msg_d7a71e7b5001aDNBj0MbW6Hr29","sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a71edc4857f34271a8dbd95b8f7da913","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Kubernetes provider service.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import logging\n4: import re\n5: import time\n6: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n7: \n8: try:\n9:     from kubernetes import client, config\n10:     from kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n11:     KUBERNETES_AVAILABLE = True\n12: except ImportError:\n13:     KUBERNETES_AVAILABLE = False\n14:     client = None\n15:     config = None\n16:     ApiException = Exception\n17: \n18: \n19: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n20: \n21: \n22: class KubernetesProvider:\n23:     \"\"\"Provider for deploying agents to standard Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n24: \n25:     def __init__(\n26:         self,\n27:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n28:         verbose: bool = False,\n29:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n30:     ) -> None:\n31:         \"\"\"Initialize the Kubernetes provider.\"\"\"\n32:         self.namespace = namespace\n33:         self.verbose = verbose\n34:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n35: \n36:         if not KUBERNETES_AVAILABLE:\n37:             raise RuntimeError(\n38:                 \"Kubernetes Python client is not installed. \"\n39:                 \"Install it with: pip install kubernetes\"\n40:             )\n41: \n42:         if verbose:\n43:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n44: \n45:         self._load_config()\n46:         self._core_v1 = client.CoreV1Api()\n47:         self._apps_v1 = client.AppsV1Api()\n48: \n49:     def _load_config(self) -> None:\n50:         \"\"\"Load Kubernetes configuration.\"\"\"\n51:         try:\n52:             if self.kubeconfig:\n53:                 config.load_kube_config(config_file=self.kubeconfig)\n54:             else:\n55:                 config.load_kube_config()\n56:         except config.ConfigException:\n57:             try:\n58:                 config.load_incluster_config()\n59:             except config.ConfigException as e:\n60:                 raise RuntimeError(\n61:                     \"Failed to load Kubernetes configuration. \"\n62:                     \"Please provide a kubeconfig file or run in a Kubernetes cluster.\"\n63:                 ) from e\n64: \n65:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n66:         \"\"\"Ensure the namespace exists.\"\"\"\n67:         try:\n68:             self._core_v1.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n69:         except ApiException as e:\n70:             if e.status == 404:\n71:                 namespace = client.V1Namespace(\n72:                     metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n73:                 )\n74:                 self._core_v1.create_namespace(namespace)\n75:                 logger.info(f\"Created namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n76:             else:\n77:                 raise\n78: \n79:     def deploy_agent(\n80:         self,\n81:         agent_name: str,\n82:         image_url: str,\n83:         port: int,\n84:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n85:         replicas: int = 1,\n86:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n87:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n88:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n89:         \"\"\"Deploy an agent to Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n90:         self._ensure_namespace()\n91: \n92:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n93: \n94:         env_list = [\n95:             client.V1EnvVar(name=k, value=v) for k, v in (env_vars or {}).items()\n96:         ]\n97: \n98:         container = client.V1Container(\n99:             name=sanitized_name,\n100:             image=image_url,\n101:             ports=[client.V1ContainerPort(container_port=port)],\n102:             env=env_list,\n103:         )\n104: \n105:         deployment = self._create_deployment(\n106:             sanitized_name, image_url, port, entrypoint, replicas, env_vars\n107:         )\n108: \n109:         service = self._create_service(sanitized_name, port, node_port)\n110: \n111:         self.wait_for_deployment_ready(sanitized_name, timeout=120)\n112: \n113:         result = {\n114:             \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name,\n115:             \"service_name\": sanitized_name,\n116:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n117:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n118:             \"container_port\": port,\n119:             \"node_port\": service.spec.ports[0].node_port,\n120:             \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{service.spec.ports[0].node_port}\",\n121:         }\n122: \n123:         logger.info(f\"Successfully deployed agent {sanitized_name}\")\n124:         return result\n125: \n126:     def _create_deployment(\n127:         self,\n128:         name: str,\n129:         image_url: str,\n130:         port: int,\n131:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n132:         replicas: int,\n133:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n134:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n135:         \"\"\"Create a Kubernetes deployment.\"\"\"\n136:         env_list = [\n137:             client.V1EnvVar(name=k, value=v) for k, v in (env_vars or {}).items()\n138:         ]\n139: \n140:         container = client.V1Container(\n141:             name=name,\n142:             image=image_url,\n143:             ports=[client.V1ContainerPort(container_port=port)],\n144:             env=env_list,\n145:         )\n146: \n147:         template = client.V1PodTemplateSpec(\n148:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(labels={\"app\": name}),\n149:             spec=client.V1PodSpec(containers=[container]),\n150:         )\n151: \n152:         spec = client.V1DeploymentSpec(\n153:             replicas=replicas,\n154:             template=template,\n155:             selector=client.V1LabelSelector(match_labels={\"app\": name}),\n156:         )\n157: \n158:         deployment = client.V1Deployment(\n159:             api_version=\"apps/v1\",\n160:             kind=\"Deployment\",\n161:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=name, namespace=self.namespace),\n162:             spec=spec,\n163:         )\n164: \n165:         try:\n166:             self._apps_v1.create_namespaced_deployment(self.namespace, deployment)\n167:             logger.info(f\"Created deployment {name}\")\n168:         except ApiException as e:\n169:             if e.status == 409:\n170:                 self._apps_v1.replace_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace, deployment)\n171:                 logger.info(f\"Updated deployment {name}\")\n172:             else:\n173:                 raise\n174: \n175:         return deployment.to_dict()\n176: \n177:     def _create_service(\n178:         self,\n179:         name: str,\n180:         port: int,\n181:         node_port: Optional[int],\n182:     ) -> client.V1Service:\n183:         \"\"\"Create a Kubernetes NodePort service.\"\"\"\n184:         service = client.V1Service(\n185:             api_version=\"v1\",\n186:             kind=\"Service\",\n187:             metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=name, namespace=self.namespace),\n188:             spec=client.V1ServiceSpec(\n189:                 type=\"NodePort\",\n190:                 selector={\"app\": name},\n191:                 ports=[\n192:                     client.V1ServicePort(\n193:                         port=port,\n194:                         target_port=port,\n195:                         node_port=node_port,\n196:                     )\n197:                 ],\n198:             ),\n199:         )\n200: \n201:         try:\n202:             created = self._core_v1.create_namespaced_service(self.namespace, service)\n203:             logger.info(f\"Created service {name}\")\n204:         except ApiException as e:\n205:             if e.status == 409:\n206:                 created = self._core_v1.replace_namespaced_service(name, self.namespace, service)\n207:                 logger.info(f\"Updated service {name}\")\n208:             else:\n209:                 raise\n210: \n211:         return created\n212: \n213:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n214:         \"\"\"Wait for a deployment to be ready.\"\"\"\n215:         start_time = time.time()\n216: \n217:         while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n218:             try:\n219:                 deployment = self._apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n220:                 if (\n221:                     deployment.status.ready_replicas is not None\n222:                     and deployment.status.ready_replicas >= deployment.spec.replicas\n223:                 ):\n224:                     logger.info(f\"Deployment {name} is ready\")\n225:                     return\n226:             except ApiException as e:\n227:                 logger.warning(f\"Error checking deployment status: {e}\")\n228: \n229:             time.sleep(2)\n230: \n231:         raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout} seconds\")\n232: \n233:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n234:         \"\"\"Get the status of an agent deployment.\"\"\"\n235:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n236: \n237:         try:\n238:             deployment = self._apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n239:             return {\n240:                 \"status\": \"running\",\n241:                 \"replicas\": deployment.spec.replicas,\n242:                 \"ready_replicas\": deployment.status.ready_replicas or 0,\n243:                 \"available_replicas\": deployment.status.available_replicas or 0,\n244:             }\n245:         except ApiException as e:\n246:             if e.status == 404:\n247:                 return {\"status\": \"not_found\"}\n248:             raise\n249: \n250:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n251:         \"\"\"Delete an agent deployment.\"\"\"\n252:         sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n253: \n254:         try:\n255:             self._apps_v1.delete_namespaced_deployment(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n256:             logger.info(f\"Deleted deployment {sanitized_name}\")\n257:         except ApiException as e:\n258:             if e.status != 404:\n259:                 logger.warning(f\"Failed to delete deployment: {e}\")\n260: \n261:         try:\n262:             self._core_v1.delete_namespaced_service(sanitized_name, self.namespace)\n263:             logger.info(f\"Deleted service {sanitized_name}\")\n264:         except ApiException as e:\n265:             if e.status != 404:\n266:                 logger.warning(f\"Failed to delete service: {e}\")\n267: \n268:         return {\n269:             \"status\": \"deleted\",\n270:             \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name,\n271:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n272:         }\n273: \n274:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n275:         \"\"\"Sanitize a name for Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n276:         sanitized = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", name.lower())\n277:         sanitized = re.sub(r\"-+\", \"-\", sanitized)\n278:         sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n279:         if len(sanitized) > 63:\n280:             sanitized = sanitized[:63].rstrip(\"-\")\n281:         return sanitized or \"agent\"\n\n(End of file - total 281 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Kubernetes provider service.\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nimport re\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\ntry:\n    from kubernetes import client, config\n    from kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n    KUBERNETES_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    KUBERNETES_AVAILABLE = False\n    client = None\n    config = None\n    ApiException = Exception\n\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py","time":{"start":1775875792533,"end":1775875792554}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875792557,"sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a72129b001NJ75umfbOFT6IG","messageID":"msg_d7a71e7b5001aDNBj0MbW6Hr29","sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f8cb7d23743a443badb7b3c7cab4f712","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Main CLI module for AgentCube using Typer.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import json\n4: import logging\n5: import os\n6: import sys\n7: import traceback\n8: from pathlib import Path\n9: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n10: \n11: import typer\n12: from rich.console import Console\n13: from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n14: \n15: from agentcube import __version__\n16: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n17: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n18: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n19: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n20: from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n21: \n22: app = typer.Typer(\n23:     name=\"agentcube\",\n24:     help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\",\n25:     no_args_is_help=True,\n26:     rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n27:     add_completion=False,\n28: )\n29: \n30: console = Console()\n31: \n32: \n33: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n34:     \"\"\"Display version and exit.\"\"\"\n35:     if value:\n36:         console.print(f\"[bold green]AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}[/]\")\n37:         raise typer.Exit()\n38: \n39: \n40: @app.callback()\n41: def main(\n42:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n43:         None,\n44:         \"--version\",\n45:         help=\"Show version and exit\",\n46:         callback=version_callback,\n47:         is_eager=True,\n48:     ),\n49:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n50: ) -> None:\n51:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n52:     if verbose:\n53:         logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n54: \n55: \n56: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n57:     \"\"\"Handle errors consistently across commands.\"\"\"\n58:     console.print(f\"[bold red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/]\")\n59:     if verbose:\n60:         console.print(\"[bold red]Traceback:[/]\")\n61:         traceback.print_exc()\n62:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n63: \n64: \n65: @app.command()\n66: def pack(\n67:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n68:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n69:     ),\n70:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n71:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n72:         None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"\n73:     ),\n74:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n75:         None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"\n76:     ),\n77:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n78:         None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"\n79:     ),\n80:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n81:         None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"\n82:     ),\n83:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n84:         None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"\n85:     ),\n86:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n87:         None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"\n88:     ),\n89:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n90: ) -> None:\n91:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace by validating and preparing it.\"\"\"\n92:     try:\n93:         if verbose:\n94:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n95: \n96:         runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n97:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n98: \n99:         with Progress(\n100:             SpinnerColumn(),\n101:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n102:             console=console,\n103:         ) as progress:\n104:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n105: \n106:             options: Dict[str, Any] = {\n107:                 \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n108:                 \"language\": language,\n109:                 \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n110:                 \"port\": port,\n111:                 \"build_mode\": build_mode,\n112:                 \"description\": description,\n113:                 \"output\": output,\n114:             }\n115: \n116:             result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n117: \n118:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Packaging complete!\", completed=True)\n119: \n120:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully packaged agent\")\n121:         console.print(f\"  Agent name: [cyan]{result['agent_name']}[/]\")\n122:         console.print(f\"  Workspace: [cyan]{result['workspace_path']}[/]\")\n123:         console.print(f\"  Metadata: [cyan]{result['metadata_path']}[/]\")\n124: \n125:     except Exception as e:\n126:         _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n127: \n128: \n129: @app.command()\n130: def build(\n131:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n132:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n133:     ),\n134:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n135:         None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"\n136:     ),\n137:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n138:         None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n139:     ),\n140:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n141:         None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"\n142:     ),\n143:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n144: ) -> None:\n145:     \"\"\"Build a container image from the packaged agent workspace.\"\"\"\n146:     try:\n147:         if verbose:\n148:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n149: \n150:         runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n151:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n152: \n153:         with Progress(\n154:             SpinnerColumn(),\n155:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n156:             console=console,\n157:         ) as progress:\n158:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Building image...\", total=None)\n159: \n160:             options: Dict[str, Any] = {\n161:                 \"proxy\": proxy,\n162:                 \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n163:                 \"output\": output,\n164:             }\n165: \n166:             result = runtime.build(workspace_path, **options)\n167: \n168:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Build complete!\", completed=True)\n169: \n170:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully built image\")\n171:         console.print(f\"  Image name: [cyan]{result['image_name']}[/]\")\n172:         console.print(f\"  Image ID: [cyan]{result['image_id']}[/]\")\n173:         console.print(f\"  Image size: [cyan]{result['image_size']}[/]\")\n174: \n175:     except Exception as e:\n176:         _handle_error(e, \"building image\", verbose)\n177: \n178: \n179: @app.command()\n180: def publish(\n181:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n182:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n183:     ),\n184:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n185:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"\n186:     ),\n187:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n188:         None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"\n189:     ),\n190:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n191:         None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"\n192:     ),\n193:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n194:         None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"\n195:     ),\n196:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n197:         None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"\n198:     ),\n199:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n200:         None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"\n201:     ),\n202:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n203:         None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n204:     ),\n205:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n206:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n207:     ),\n208:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n209:         None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"\n210:     ),\n211:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n212:         None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment\"\n213:     ),\n214:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n215:         None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"\n216:     ),\n217:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n218: ) -> None:\n219:     \"\"\"Publish an agent to the specified provider.\"\"\"\n220:     try:\n221:         if verbose:\n222:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n223: \n224:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n225:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n226: \n227:         with Progress(\n228:             SpinnerColumn(),\n229:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n230:             console=console,\n231:         ) as progress:\n232:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Publishing agent...\", total=None)\n233: \n234:             options: Dict[str, Any] = {\n235:                 \"version\": version,\n236:                 \"image_url\": image_url,\n237:                 \"image_username\": image_username,\n238:                 \"image_password\": image_password,\n239:                 \"description\": description,\n240:                 \"region\": region,\n241:                 \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n242:                 \"node_port\": node_port,\n243:                 \"replicas\": replicas,\n244:                 \"namespace\": namespace,\n245:             }\n246: \n247:             result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)\n248: \n249:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Publish complete!\", completed=True)\n250: \n251:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully published agent\")\n252:         console.print(f\"  Agent ID: [cyan]{result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}[/]\")\n253:         console.print(f\"  Endpoint: [cyan]{result.get('endpoint', 'N/A')}[/]\")\n254: \n255:     except Exception as e:\n256:         _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n257: \n258: \n259: @app.command()\n260: def invoke(\n261:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n262:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n263:     ),\n264:     payload: str = typer.Option(\n265:         \"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"\n266:     ),\n267:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(\n268:         None,\n269:         \"--header\",\n270:         help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\",\n271:     ),\n272:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n273:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n274:     ),\n275:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n276: ) -> None:\n277:     \"\"\"Invoke a published agent with the given payload.\"\"\"\n278:     try:\n279:         if verbose:\n280:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n281: \n282:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n283: \n284:         try:\n285:             payload_data: Dict[str, Any] = json.loads(payload)\n286:         except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n287:             console.print(f\"[bold red]Invalid JSON payload: {e}[/]\")\n288:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n289: \n290:         headers: Dict[str, str] = {}\n291:         if header_list:\n292:             for header in header_list:\n293:                 if \":\" not in header:\n294:                     console.print(f\"[bold red]Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value', got: {header}[/]\")\n295:                     raise typer.Exit(1)\n296:                 key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n297:                 headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n298: \n299:         runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n300: \n301:         with Progress(\n302:             SpinnerColumn(),\n303:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n304:             console=console,\n305:         ) as progress:\n306:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n307: \n308:             result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_data, headers)\n309: \n310:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Invoke complete!\", completed=True)\n311: \n312:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Successfully invoked agent\")\n313:         console.print(f\"  Response: [cyan]{json.dumps(result, indent=2)}[/]\")\n314: \n315:     except typer.Exit:\n316:         raise\n317:     except Exception as e:\n318:         _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n319: \n320: \n321: @app.command()\n322: def status(\n323:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n324:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True\n325:     ),\n326:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n327:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n328:     ),\n329:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n330: ) -> None:\n331:     \"\"\"Get the status of a published agent.\"\"\"\n332:     try:\n333:         if verbose:\n334:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n335: \n336:         runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n337:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n338: \n339:         with Progress(\n340:             SpinnerColumn(),\n341:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n342:             console=console,\n343:         ) as progress:\n344:             task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Getting status...\", total=None)\n345: \n346:             result = runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider)\n347: \n348:             progress.update(task, description=\"[cyan]Status retrieved!\", completed=True)\n349: \n350:         if result[\"status\"] in (\"not_published\", \"error\"):\n351:             console.print(f\"[bold red]✗[/] Agent status: {result['status']}[/]\")\n352:             if result[\"status\"] == \"not_published\":\n353:                 console.print(\"  Please publish the agent first using 'agentcube publish'\")\n354:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n355: \n356:         console.print(f\"[bold green]✓[/] Agent status: {result['status']}[/]\")\n357:         for key, value in result.items():\n358:             if