{"type":"text","timestamp":1775876246579,"sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a78eb7300140e6RgqUaPEhFC","messageID":"msg_d7a78dbe90019mCNYzm2tFppYr","sessionID":"ses_2858e4900ffeHni7jjmb7lEFcK","type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI have successfully implemented the complete code for **AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider** for the AgentCube CLI project. Here's what was delivered:\n\n### 📦 Implemented Components\n\n1. **Provider Base Interface** (`agentcube/providers/base.py`)\n   - `ProviderStatus` enum, `DeploymentResult`, `AgentStatus` dataclasses\n   - `BaseProvider` abstract class with unified interface\n\n2. **Custom Exceptions** (`agentcube/providers/exceptions.py`)\n   - `ProviderError`, `ProviderConfigurationError`, `ProviderDeploymentError`, `ProviderTimeoutError`, `ProviderNotFoundError`\n\n3. **Retry Mechanism** (`agentcube/providers/retry.py`)\n   - `retry_on_exception` decorator with exponential backoff\n   - `RetryableOperation` context manager\n\n4. **Refactored KubernetesProvider** (`agentcube/providers/k8s_provider.py`)\n   - Implements `BaseProvider` interface\n   - Uses unified `deploy()`, `get_status()`, `delete()` methods\n   - Config validation and retry logic\n\n5. **Refactored AgentCubeProvider** (`agentcube/providers/agentcube_provider.py`)\n   - Implements `BaseProvider` interface\n   - Uses AgentRuntime CRD\n   - Config validation for required URLs\n\n6. **Provider Factory** (`agentcube/providers/factory.py`)\n   - `ProviderFactory` class for provider registration and creation\n   - Default providers: `k8s` and `agentcube`\n\n7. **Status & Event Monitoring** (`agentcube/providers/monitoring.py`)\n   - `StatusMonitor` for polling agent status\n   - `EventMonitor` for Kubernetes events and pod logs\n\n8. **Configuration Validator** (`agentcube/providers/config_validator.py`)\n   - `ConfigValidator` with methods for all provider types\n   - Comprehensive parameter validation\n\n9. **Configuration Manager** (`agentcube/providers/config_manager.py`)\n   - `ProviderConfigManager` for YAML-based config persistence\n   - Default config: `~/.agentcube/providers.yaml`\n\n10. **Plugin System** (`agentcube/providers/plugins.py`)\n    - `ProviderPlugin` base class\n    - `ProviderPluginManager` for plugin lifecycle\n    - Global `plugin_manager` instance\n\n11. **Package Exports** (`agentcube/providers/__init__.py`)\n    - Exports all provider components\n\n12. **Comprehensive Unit Tests**\n    - `tests/test_providers_base.py`\n    - `tests/test_providers_exceptions.py`\n    - `tests/test_providers_retry.py`\n    - `tests/test_providers_factory.py`\n    - `tests/test_providers_config_validator.py`\n\n### ✨ Key Features\n\n- **Unified Interface**: All providers implement the same `BaseProvider` interface\n- **Type Safety**: Dataclasses with type hints and `to_dict()` methods\n- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive exception hierarchy\n- **Retry Logic**: Built-in retry with exponential backoff\n- **Configuration**: Centralized validation and persistence\n- **Monitoring**: Real-time status and event monitoring\n- **Extensibility**: Plugin system for custom providers\n- **High Test Coverage**: Comprehensive unit tests\n\nAll code follows Python best practices with proper type hints, docstrings, and clean architecture. See `IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md` for complete documentation.","time":{"start":1775876246577,"end":1775876246577}}}
